cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE

This paper deals with natural language processing and semantic interpretation tasks, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a set of semantic roles that can be used in the development of information extraction frameworks and semantic models, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the syntactic configuration of dictionary definitions, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language generation (cs.NE).
